<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="734" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/563: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-26T17:00:00-05:00">February 26, 1936—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>25. Unless you perceive objection, please communicate to the Japanese
                            Minister for Foreign Affairs as from me a message reading as follows:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“On behalf of the American Government and people I assure you of
                                    the deep regret with which we have learned of the death of
                                    distinguished officials of the Japanese Government and I extend
                                    to you our sincere condolences.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Report action by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>